        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare multiple congenital anomalies/dysmorphic syndrome without intellectual disability characterized by congenital heart disease skeletal and joint abnormalities (including pectus excavatum scoliosis and hyper-extensibility or contractures in finger joints) variable dysmorphic facial features (notably long face with narrow maxilla and pointed chin) and failure to thrive. Addinitonal clinical features may include gastrointestinal problems lipodystrophy&#8208;like features renal hypoplasia hearing impairment distinct ocular abnormalities thin/velvety skin risk for pneumothorax and genital abnormalities in male."
        },
